419 /*--------------------------------------------------------
420  * Linear Equation Subroutine
421  * GMRES (Generalized Minimum Residual)
422  * Cf. C.T.Kelley: Iterative Methods for Linear and Nonlinear Equations
423  * T.Ohtsuka '00/01/24
424  * axfunc(unsigned n, double *x, double *ax): a function that gives A*x
425  * n: dim x
426  * b: the right-hand-side of the equation, A*x = b
427  * x: initial guess, to be replaced with the solution
428  * kmax: number of iteration
429  * err: residual norms, |b - A*x_i| (i=1,...,n+1)
430  * ----------------------------------------------------------*/
431 void Cmscgmres::nfgmres(funcptr_cgmresfunc axfunc, unsigned n, double *b,
432  double *x, unsigned kmax, double *err) {
433  int i,j,k;
434  double rho, nu, normv_unorth,hr;
435  double *cvec, *svec, *gvec, *tmpvec, **hmat, **vmat;
436 
437  cvec = defvector(kmax+1);
438  svec = defvector(kmax+1);
439  gvec = defvector(kmax+1);
440  tmpvec = defvector(n);
441  hmat = defmatrix(kmax+1,kmax+1);
442  vmat = defmatrix(kmax+1, n);
443 
444  (this->*axfunc)(n, x, tmpvec);
445  msub(1,n, b, tmpvec, tmpvec);
446  rho = sqrt(mvinner(n, tmpvec, tmpvec));
447  gvec[0] = rho;
448  for(i=1; i<kmax+1; i++){
449  gvec[i] = 0;
450  }
451  err[0] = rho;
452 
453  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
454  printf(" Rho =%f\n",rho);
455  }
456 
457  //If rho=0. Given Control is optimal -> Do nothing
458  if(rho!=0){
459 
460  if(std::isnan(rho)){
461  rho=1/rtol_;
462  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
463  printf("GMRES: rho=nan => inequality violated=> set rho=1/rtol=%f \n",rho);
464  }
465  }
466 
467  mdivsc(1,n, tmpvec, rho, vmat[0]);
468 
469  for(k=0; ((k<kmax)&&(rho>rtol_)); k++){
470  (this->*axfunc)(n, vmat[k], vmat[k+1]);
471  normv_unorth=sqrt(mvinner(n, vmat[k+1], vmat[k+1]));
472  /* Modified Gram-Schmidt */
473  for(j=0; j<=k; j++){
474  hmat[k][j] = mvinner(n, vmat[j], vmat[k+1]);
475  mmulsc(1,n, vmat[j], hmat[k][j], tmpvec);
476  msub(1,n, vmat[k+1], tmpvec, vmat[k+1]);
477  }
478  hmat[k][k+1] = sqrt(mvinner(n, vmat[k+1], vmat[k+1]));
479 
480  //REORTHOGONALIZE:: If norm_unorth + 0.001*norm_orth==1
481  if((normv_unorth + .0001*hmat[k][k+1])==normv_unorth){
482  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
483  // printf("GMRES::Reorthogonalize/n");
484  printf("GMRES::Reorthogonalize as normv_unorth + .0001*hmat[k][k+1]==%f==%f==normv_unorth /n",(normv_unorth + .0001*hmat[k][k+1]),normv_unorth);
485  }
486  for(j=0; j<=k; j++){
487  hr=mvinner(n, vmat[j], vmat[k+1]);
488  hmat[k][j]=hmat[k][j]+hr;
489  mmulsc(1,n, vmat[j], hr, tmpvec);
490  msub(1,n, vmat[k+1], tmpvec, vmat[k+1]);
491  }
492  hmat[k][k+1] = sqrt(mvinner(n, vmat[k+1], vmat[k+1]));
493  }
494 
495  /* No Breakdown? */
496  if( hmat[k][k+1] != 0){
497  mdivsc(1,n, vmat[k+1], hmat[k][k+1], vmat[k+1]);
498  }
499  else{
500  /*Happy Breakdown*/
501  mmov(1,n,vmat[k+1],x);
502  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
503  printf("gmress() :happy breakdown \n");
504  }
505  freevector(cvec);
506  freevector(svec);
507  freevector(gvec);
508  freevector(tmpvec);
509  freematrix(hmat);
510  freematrix(vmat);
511 
512  return;
513  }
514 
515  /* Givens Rotation */
516  givrot(k, cvec, svec, hmat[k]);
517  nu = sqrt(hmat[k][k] * hmat[k][k] + hmat[k][k+1] * hmat[k][k+1]);
518  if( nu != 0 ){
519  cvec[k] = hmat[k][k] / nu;
520  svec[k] = - hmat[k][k+1] / nu;
521  hmat[k][k] = cvec[k] * hmat[k][k] - svec[k] * hmat[k][k+1];
522  hmat[k][k+1] = 0;
523  givrot(1, cvec+k, svec+k, gvec+k);
524  }
525  else{
526  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
527  printf("nu is zero!\n");
528  }
529  }
530 
531  /* Residual Update */
532  rho = fabs(gvec[k+1]);
533  err[k+1] = rho;
534  }
535 
536 
537  /* Solve hmat * y = gvec (hmat: upper triangular) */
538  for(i=k-1; i>=0; i--){
539  for(nu=gvec[i], j=i+1; j<k; j++){
540  nu -= hmat[j][i] * cvec[j];
541  }
542  cvec[i] = nu / hmat[i][i] ;
543  /* for(nu=0, j=i+1; j<k; j++){
544  nu += hmat[j][i] * cvec[j];
545  }
546  cvec[i] = (gvec[i] - nu) / hmat[i][i] ;*/
547  }
548  /* Ans. */
549  for(i=0; i<n; i++){
550  for(nu=0, j=0; j<k; j++){
551  nu += vmat[j][i] * cvec[j];
552  }
553  x[i] += nu;
554  }
555  }
556  else{
557  if(flag_show_controllerinfo_){
558  printf(" CGMRES rho=0 ->optimal\n");
559  }
560  }
561  freevector(cvec);
562  freevector(svec);
563  freevector(gvec);
564  freevector(tmpvec);
565  freematrix(hmat);
566  freematrix(vmat);
567 }

905 /*---- k Givens Roations used in GMRES ----*/
906 void Cmscgmres::givrot(unsigned k, double *c, double *s, double *v) {
907  unsigned i;
908  double w1, w2;
909  for (i = 0; i < k; i++) {
910  w1 = c[i] * v[i] - s[i] * v[i + 1];
911  w2 = s[i] * v[i] + c[i] * v[i + 1];

917 /*--------------------------------------------------------
918  * Simultaneous Ordinaly Diferential Equation Subroutine
919  * Runge-Kutta_Gill Method (Original by T.Murayama)
920  *
921  * ---- Variation of rkg() : dx/dt is also returned. ----
922  * ---- (for Start of the Adams method) ----
923  * ----------------------------------------------------------*/
924 void Cmscgmres::nfrkginpex(funcPtr_func func, double x, double* y, double* u, double h, unsigned dim, double* ans, double* fxy)
925 {
926  int i;
927  double fval[dim],k1[dim],k2[dim],k3[dim],k4[dim],
928  yp1[dim],yp2[dim],yp3[dim],
929  q1[dim],q2[dim],q3[dim],
930  c1 = 0.2928932188134528,
931  c2 = 0.1213203435596426,
932  c3 = 0.5857864376269054,
933  c4 = 1.707106781186548,
934  c5 = 4.121320343559643,
935  c6 = 3.414213562373097;
936 
937  /* fval = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
938  k1 = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
939  k2 = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
940  k3 = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
941  k4 = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
942  */
943 
944  (this->*func)(x,y,u,fxy);
945  for(i = 0; i < dim; i++)
946  {
947  k1[i] = h * fxy[i];
948  yp1[i] = y[i] + 0.5 * k1[i];
949  q1[i] = k1[i];
950  }
951  (this->*func)(x + 0.5 * h,yp1,u,fval);
952  for(i = 0; i < dim; i++)
953  {
954  k2[i] = h * fval[i];
955  yp2[i] = yp1[i] + c1 * (k2[i] - q1[i]);;
956  q2[i] = c2 * q1[i] + c3 * k2[i];
957  }
958  (this->*func)(x + 0.5 * h,yp2,u,fval);
959  for(i = 0; i < dim; i++)
960  {
961  k3[i] = h * fval[i];
962  yp3[i] = yp2[i] + c4 * (k3[i] - q2[i]);
963  q3[i] = -c5 * q2[i] + c6 * k3[i];
964  }
965  (this->*func)(x + h,yp3,u,fval);
966  for(i = 0; i < dim; i++)
967  {
968  k4[i] = h * fval[i];
969  ans[i] = yp3[i] + k4[i] / 6.0 - q3[i] / 3.0;
970  }
971 }

973 /*--------------------------------------------------------
974  * Simultaneous Ordinaly Diferential Equation Subroutine
975  * Adams Method (Predictor-Corrector Method)
976  * Predictor: Adams-Bashforth
977  * Corrector: Adams-Moulton
978  * T.Ohtsuka '92/10/24
979  * ----------------------------------------------------------*/
980 void Cmscgmres::nfadamsinp(funcPtr_func func, double x, double* y, double* u, double* f1, double* f2, double* f3, double h, unsigned dim,double* ans)
981 {
982  int i;
983  double y1[dim], fval[dim], cd;
984  /* double *y1, *fval, cd;
985 
986  fval = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) );
987  y1 = (double *)malloc( (size_t)( dim * sizeof(double) ) ); */
988  cd = h / 24.;
989 
990  /*---- Adams-Bashforth Predictor ----*/
991  (this->*func)(x,y,u,fval);
992  for(i=0; i<dim; i++)
993  {
994  y1[i] = 55.* fval[i] -59.* f1[i] +37.* f2[i] -9.* f3[i];
995  y1[i] *= cd;
996  y1[i] += y[i];
997  f3[i] = f2[i]; f2[i] = f1[i]; f1[i] = fval[i]; /* Shift */
998  }
999 
1000  /*---- Adams-Moulton Corrector ----*/
1001  (this->*func)(x+h,y1,u,fval);
